Brits Five people were arrested for attempted murder and attempted house robbery at a farm near Brits, North West police said on Tuesday.&nbsp; Colonel Emelda Setlhako said the men, age 24 to 38, were arrested on Friday, after they attempted to gain entrance into a farm house in Rooikoppies near Brits.&nbsp; &quot;The suspects allegedly shot the farm owner who was outside the house in the leg and ran away. One of them was found dead with a bullet wound outside the yard. Investigations into the matter continue,&quot; she said. It was not clear who shot the intruder.&nbsp; The five suspects were expected to appear in the Brits Magistrate's Court on Wednesday.&nbsp; ANA